## Summary: OpenClaw Channel Plugin SDK & Manifest Format

I've gathered the complete plugin manifest format and SDK contracts for channel plugins in OpenClaw. Here's the comprehensive reference:

---

### 1. **Plugin Manifest Format** (`openclaw.plugin.json`)

**Location**: `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775467524242-gn0vo7/docs/plugins/manifest.md`

Every OpenClaw plugin must ship an `openclaw.plugin.json` in the plugin root. For channel plugins, the minimal required structure is:

```json
{
  "id": "channel-id",
  "channels": ["channel-id"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Full optional fields**:
- `id` (required): Canonical plugin id
- `channels` (optional): Array of channel ids owned by this plugin
- `configSchema` (required): JSON Schema for plugin config
- `name`: Human-readable name
- `description`: Short summary
- `version`: Informational version
- `uiHints`: UI labels/placeholders/sensitivity for config fields
- `enabledByDefault`: Mark bundled plugin as enabled by default
- `providerAuthChoices`: Auth metadata for onboarding
- `providerAuthEnvVars`: Cheap provider-auth env metadata
- `contracts`: Static capability ownership snapshot
- `kind`: Exclusive plugin kind ("memory" or "context-engine")

**Real bundled channel examples**:
- IRC, Matrix, Telegram, Nostr, Zalo, Slack all use the minimal structure with just `id`, `channels`, and `configSchema`

---

### 2. **Core Type Definitions**

**Location 1**: `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775467524242-gn0vo7/src/channels/plugins/types.plugin.ts`

The main `ChannelPlugin` interface that every channel must implement:

```typescript
type ChannelPlugin<ResolvedAccount = any, Probe = unknown, Audit = unknown> = {
  id: ChannelId;
  meta: ChannelMeta;
  capabilities: ChannelCapabilities;

  // Optional features
  defaults?: { queue?: { debounceMs?: number } };
  reload?: { configPrefixes: string[]; noopPrefixes?: string[] };
  setupWizard?: ChannelPluginSetupWizard;
  config: ChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;
  configSchema?: ChannelConfigSchema;
  setup?: ChannelSetupAdapter;
  pairing?: ChannelPairingAdapter;
  security?: ChannelSecurityAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;
  groups?: ChannelGroupAdapter;
  mentions?: ChannelMentionAdapter;
  outbound?: ChannelOutboundAdapter;
  status?: ChannelStatusAdapter<ResolvedAccount, Probe, Audit>;
  gatewayMethods?: string[];
  gateway?: ChannelGatewayAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;
  auth?: ChannelAuthAdapter;
  approvalCapability?: ChannelApprovalCapability;
  elevated?: ChannelElevatedAdapter;
  commands?: ChannelCommandAdapter;
  lifecycle?: ChannelLifecycleAdapter;
  approvals?: ChannelApprovalAdapter;
  allowlist?: ChannelAllowlistAdapter;
  bindings?: ChannelConfiguredBindingProvider;
  conversationBindings?: ChannelConversationBindingSupport;
  streaming?: ChannelStreamingAdapter;
  threading?: ChannelThreadingAdapter;
  messaging?: ChannelMessagingAdapter;
  agentPrompt?: ChannelAgentPromptAdapter;
  directory?: ChannelDirectoryAdapter;
  resolver?: ChannelResolverAdapter;
  actions?: ChannelMessageActionAdapter;
  heartbeat?: ChannelHeartbeatAdapter;
  agentTools?: ChannelAgentToolFactory | ChannelAgentTool[];
};
```

**Key supporting types**:

```typescript
// Metadata
type ChannelMeta = {
  id: ChannelId;
  label: string;
  selectionLabel: string;
  docsPath: string;
  docsLabel?: string;
  blurb: string;
  order?: number;
  aliases?: readonly string[];
  selectionDocsPrefix?: string;
  detailLabel?: string;
  systemImage?: string;
  markdownCapable?: boolean;
  showConfigured?: boolean;
  quickstartAllowFrom?: boolean;
  forceAccountBinding?: boolean;
};

// Static capabilities
type ChannelCapabilities = {
  chatTypes: Array<ChatType | "thread">;
  polls?: boolean;
  reactions?: boolean;
  edit?: boolean;
  unsend?: boolean;
  reply?: boolean;
  effects?: boolean;
  groupManagement?: boolean;
  threads?: boolean;
  media?: boolean;
  nativeCommands?: boolean;
  blockStreaming?: boolean;
};

// Config schema (JSON Schema + UI hints + runtime validation)
type ChannelConfigSchema = {
  schema: Record<string, unknown>;
  uiHints?: Record<string, ChannelConfigUiHint>;
  runtime?: ChannelConfigRuntimeSchema;
};

type ChannelConfigUiHint = {
  label?: string;
  help?: string;
  tags?: string[];
  advanced?: boolean;
  sensitive?: boolean;
  placeholder?: string;
  itemTemplate?: unknown;
};
```

---

### 3. **Core Adapter Contracts**

**Location**: `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775467524242-gn0vo7/src/channels/plugins/types.adapters.ts` (3000+ lines)

Key adapters:

**ChannelSetupAdapter**: Account resolution and setup wizard
```typescript
type ChannelSetupAdapter = {
  resolveAccountId?: (params) => string;
  applyAccountConfig: (params) => OpenClawConfig;
  validateInput?: (params) => string | null;
  afterAccountConfigWritten?: (params) => Promise<void> | void;
};
```

**ChannelConfigAdapter**: Account listing and resolution
```typescript
type ChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedAccount> = {
  listAccountIds: (cfg: OpenClawConfig) => string[];
  resolveAccount: (cfg: OpenClawConfig, accountId?: string | null) => ResolvedAccount;
  inspectAccount?: (cfg, accountId) => unknown;
  describeAccount?: (account, cfg) => ChannelAccountSnapshot;
  isConfigured?: (account, cfg) => boolean | Promise<boolean>;
};
```

**ChannelSecurityAdapter**: DM policy and access control
```typescript
type ChannelSecurityAdapter<ResolvedAccount = unknown> = {
  resolveDmPolicy?: (ctx: ChannelSecurityContext<ResolvedAccount>) => ChannelSecurityDmPolicy | null;
  collectWarnings?: (ctx) => Promise<string[]> | string[];
};

type ChannelSecurityDmPolicy = {
  policy: string;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number> | null;
  policyPath?: string;
  allowFromPath: string;
  approveHint: string;
  normalizeEntry?: (raw: string) => string;
};
```

**ChannelPairingAdapter**: DM approval flow
```typescript
type ChannelPairingAdapter = {
  idLabel: string;
  normalizeAllowEntry?: (entry: string) => string;
  notifyApproval?: (params) => Promise<void>;
};
```

**ChannelThreadingAdapter**: Reply threading configuration
```typescript
type ChannelThreadingAdapter = {
  resolveReplyToMode?: (params) => "off" | "first" | "all";
  allowExplicitReplyTagsWhenOff?: boolean;
  buildToolContext?: (params) => ChannelThreadingToolContext | undefined;
  resolveAutoThreadId?: (params) => string | undefined;
  resolveReplyTransport?: (params) => ChannelReplyTransport | null;
  resolveFocusedBinding?: (params) => ChannelFocusedBindingContext | null;
};
```

**ChannelOutboundAdapter**: Message sending
```typescript
type ChannelOutboundAdapter = {
  deliveryMode: "direct" | "gateway" | "hybrid";
  chunker?: ((text: string, limit: number) => string[]) | null;
  chunkerMode?: "text" | "markdown";
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  pollMaxOptions?: number;
  normalizePayload?: (params) => ReplyPayload | null;
  resolveTarget?: (params) => { ok: true; to: string } | { ok: false; error: Error };
  sendText?: (ctx: ChannelOutboundContext) => Promise<OutboundDeliveryResult>;
  sendMedia?: (ctx: ChannelOutboundContext) => Promise<OutboundDeliveryResult>;
  sendPoll?: (ctx: ChannelPollContext) => Promise<ChannelPollResult>;
};
```

**ChannelMessagingAdapter**: Target parsing and session routing
```typescript
type ChannelMessagingAdapter = {
  normalizeTarget?: (raw: string) => string | undefined;
  resolveSessionConversation?: (params) => { id: string; threadId?; baseConversationId?; parentConversationCandidates? };
  resolveSessionTarget?: (params) => string | undefined;
  inferTargetChatType?: (params) => ChatType | undefined;
  resolveOutboundSessionRoute?: (params) => ChannelOutboundSessionRoute | Promise<...> | null;
  targetResolver?: { looksLikeId?: (...) => boolean; resolveTarget?: (...) => Promise<...> };
};
```

**ChannelGatewayAdapter**: Connection/WebSocket handling
```typescript
type ChannelGatewayAdapter<ResolvedAccount = unknown> = {
  startAccount?: (ctx: ChannelGatewayContext<ResolvedAccount>) => Promise<unknown>;
  stopAccount?: (ctx: ChannelGatewayContext<ResolvedAccount>) => Promise<void>;
  loginWithQrStart?: (params) => Promise<ChannelLoginWithQrStartResult>;
  logoutAccount?: (ctx) => Promise<ChannelLogoutResult>;
};
```

**ChannelMessageActionAdapter**: Action discovery and execution for shared `message` tool
```typescript
type ChannelMessageActionAdapter = {
  describeMessageTool: (params: ChannelMessageActionDiscoveryContext) => ChannelMessageToolDiscovery | null;
  supportsAction?: (params) => boolean;
  handleAction?: (ctx: ChannelMessageActionContext) => Promise<AgentToolResult<unknown>>;
  extractToolSend?: (params) => ChannelToolSend | null;
};
```

---

### 4. **SDK Entry Point Helpers**

**Location**: `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775467524242-gn0vo7/src/plugin-sdk/core.ts`

**defineChannelPluginEntry**: Main entry point for channel plugins
```typescript
function defineChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>({
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  plugin: TPlugin;
  configSchema?: OpenClawPluginConfigSchema | (() => OpenClawPluginConfigSchema);
  setRuntime?: (runtime: PluginRuntime) => void;
  registerCliMetadata?: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void;
  registerFull?: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void;
}): DefinedChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>;
```

**createChatChannelPlugin**: High-level builder for typical chat channels
```typescript
function createChatChannelPlugin<TResolvedAccount extends { accountId?: string | null }>(params: {
  base: ChatChannelPluginBase<TResolvedAccount>;
  security?: ChannelSecurityAdapter<TResolvedAccount> | ChatChannelSecurityOptions<TResolvedAccount>;
  pairing?: ChannelPairingAdapter | ChatChannelPairingOptions;
  threading?: ChannelThreadingAdapter | ChatChannelThreadingOptions<TResolvedAccount>;
  outbound?: ChannelOutboundAdapter | ChatChannelAttachedOutboundOptions;
}): ChannelPlugin<TResolvedAccount>;
```

**createChannelPluginBase**: Base object builder
```typescript
function createChannelPluginBase<TResolvedAccount>(
  params: CreateChannelPluginBaseOptions<TResolvedAccount>
): CreatedChannelPluginBase<TResolvedAccount>;
```

**defineSetupPluginEntry**: Lightweight setup-only entry
```typescript
function defineSetupPluginEntry<TPlugin>(plugin: TPlugin): { plugin: TPlugin };
```

**Helper utilities**:
- `stripChannelTargetPrefix(raw, ...providers)`: Remove provider prefixes
- `stripTargetKindPrefix(raw)`: Remove kind prefixes (user:, group:, etc.)
- `buildChannelOutboundSessionRoute(params)`: Build canonical outbound route

