### 14. `extensions/pulseboard/src/normalize.ts`

Target normalization for PulseBoard addresses:

- `isBoardTarget(target)` — returns true if target starts with `#`
- `normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(raw)` — strips `pulseboard:`, `board:`, `user:` prefixes; prepends `#` to bare board names when `board:` prefix was used; validates format
- `looksLikePulseBoardTargetId(raw)` — basic format check (no spaces, no control chars)
- `normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(raw)` — lowercases, strips `pulseboard:` / `user:` prefixes
- `normalizePulseBoardAllowlist(entries?)` — maps entries through normalizer
- `formatPulseBoardSenderId(message)` — returns `senderUser` string
- `buildPulseBoardAllowlistCandidates(message)` — returns `[senderUser.toLowerCase()]`
- `resolvePulseBoardAllowlistMatch({ allowFrom, message })` — checks wildcard and username

---

### 15. `extensions/pulseboard/src/protocol.ts`

Low-level message and ID utilities (no external deps, pure functions):

- `makePulseBoardMessageId()` — returns UUID v4 string
- `sanitizePulseBoardOutboundText(text)` — strips NUL bytes, trims
- `parsePulseBoardServerEvent(raw)` — parses a JSON event string from the WebSocket, returns typed `PulseBoardServerEvent` discriminated union: `{ type: "message", ... }` | `{ type: "ack", ... }` | `{ type: "error", ... }`
- `buildPulseBoardSendPayload({ target, text, messageId })` — returns JSON string ready to send via WebSocket

---

### 16. `extensions/pulseboard/src/client.ts`

PulseBoard WebSocket client. No external dependencies (Node.js built-in `WebSocket` / `ws` via global). Mirrors `irc/src/client.ts` pattern:

```typescript
export interface PulseBoardClientOptions {
  serverUrl: string;
  apiKey: string;
  username: string;
  boards?: string[];
  connectTimeoutMs?: number;
  abortSignal?: AbortSignal;
  onMessage?: (event: PulseBoardServerEvent) => void | Promise<void>;
  onError?: (error: Error) => void;
  onDisconnect?: () => void;
}

export interface PulseBoardClient {
  isReady(): boolean;
  sendMessage(target: string, text: string): void; // sends board post or DM
  disconnect(reason?: string): void;
  readonly username: string;
}

export async function connectPulseBoardClient(
  opts: PulseBoardClientOptions,
): Promise<PulseBoardClient>
```

Implementation: opens WebSocket to `serverUrl`, sends `{ type: "auth", apiKey, username }` handshake, waits for `{ type: "ready" }` acknowledgement, then joins boards, resolves when ready. Times out after `connectTimeoutMs` (default 10 000 ms). Handles `abort` signal. Returns a `PulseBoardClient` with `sendMessage()` that writes `{ type: "send", to: target, text, messageId }` JSON to the socket.

---

### 17. `extensions/pulseboard/src/send.ts`

```typescript
export type SendPulseBoardResult = { messageId: string; target: string };

export async function sendMessagePulseBoard(
  to: string,
  text: string,
  opts: { cfg?: CoreConfig; accountId?: string; client?: PulseBoardClient } = {},
): Promise<SendPulseBoardResult>
```

Mirrors `irc/src/send.ts`: resolves account, normalizes target, applies markdown table conversion, uses live client from runtime if available (`getPulseBoardRuntime().channel...`), otherwise opens a transient WebSocket connection. Records outbound activity. Returns `{ messageId, target }`.

